COMMUNITY members in Mqanduli in Newtown, Eastern Cape, made a gruesome discovery on Wednesday, 6 July They discovered a newborn baby in a public toilet and called the cops. According to Sergeant Khaya Matola-Mvanyashe, police were called to the scene at about 12pm by community members after they heard a baby cry in the public toilet. “On arrival, they managed to rescue the baby and rushed her to Nelson Mandela Academic Hospital in Mthatha for medical attention. “The initial investigation indicates that the baby was dumped in the toilet, but she miraculously survived the ordeal,” said Mvanyashe. He said the baby was given the name Kungenceba, which means it is through God’s mercy that she was rescued alive in such conditions. “The circumstances surrounding the incident form part of an investigation. No arrests have been made yet, and the investigation continues,” said Mvanyashe.